                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2">
                        <p>Decorated quire marks are written in the left upper corner of the first leave of each quire (but the first one).</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>- Some of the ten psalm units, “The Canticles of the Prophets” and “The Praise of Mary” are preceded by elaborate polychrome ornamental bands, sometimes decorated with anthropomorphic motifs (fols. <locus target="#5r #27v #52r #72v #100v #117r #130r"/>unfinished on fol. <locus target="#87r"/>)</p>
                        <p>- A colour image of a prone male figure, probably the donor, is painted on fol. <locus target="#116v"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- Recent illustrations unrelated to the text are on fols. <locus target="#1"/>-<locus target="#4"/>and <locus target="#58r"/>(painted over the maint text, its the top and bottom lines remaining still visible), <locus from="170v" to="171v"/>
                        </p>
                        <p>- The blind tooled decoration of the leather cover consists of three frames with geometric pattern around a cross.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>Fol. <locus target="#5r"/>: መዝሙረ፡ዳዊት፡ትመስል፡ገነተ፡ወታስተጋብእ፡    ኵሉ፡ጽጌያተ፡ትመልእ፡ፍሬያተ፡ ወታመጽእ፡ በረከተ፨ትሰድድ፡አጋንንተ፨ወታቀርብመላእክተ፨</p>
                           <p>ተግሣጽ፡ለኵሉ።</p>
                           <p>፩፡ፍካሬ፡ዘጻድቃን፡ወዘኃጥአን።ተግሣጽ፡ለኵሉ።</p>
                           <p>መዝሙር፡ዘዳዊት፡ሃሊ፡ሉያ።</p>
                           <p>ብፁዕ፡ብእሲ፡ዘኢሖረ፡በምክረ፡ረሲዓን፨</p>
                           <p>ወዘኢቆመ፡ውስተ፡ፍኖተ፡ኃጥአን፨</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
